               <p>Second Count. Laying it not to be a lodging-room.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18000917-54-person585">
                  WILLIAM 
                  MOUNTAIN
               <interp inst="t18000917-54-person585" type="surname" value="MOUNTAIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-54-person585" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-54-person585" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I <rs id="t18000917-54-viclabel291" type="occupation">keep <placeName id="t18000917-54-crimeloc292">the White-horse-inn, in Friday-street</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-54-crimeloc292" type="placeName" value="the White-horse-inn, in Friday-street"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-54-crimeloc292" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18000917-54-off289 t18000917-54-crimeloc292"></join>
                  </rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18000917-54-victim584 t18000917-54-viclabel291"></join>: On Wednesday the 23d of July, the prisoner came to my house, ordered a supper, and a bottle of port; he asked for a bed, and came down in the morning about half past nine o'clock.</p>
               <p>Q.Did he pay for his bed? - A. He did, one shilling; he said, he wished the bed to be kept for him, for he should be back that night; he then went away, and in about twenty minutes the sheets were missing; I saw the sheets again at Guildhall on the 25th, and I saw the prisoner the same day, before I saw the sheets; they had my mark upon them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18000917-54-person586">
                  THOMAS 
                  NELSON
               <interp inst="t18000917-54-person586" type="surname" value="NELSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-54-person586" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-54-person586" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am a pawnbroker's servant, (produces a pair of sheets); I took them in of the prisoner at the bar, on the 24th of July last; I knew him by sight some years ago.</p>
               <p> 
            
                  <persName id="t18000917-54-person587">
                  WILLIAM 
                  KIMBER
               <interp inst="t18000917-54-person587" type="surname" value="KIMBER"></interp>
